    "Correspondence between QAOA on weighted and unweighted graphs with p ≥ 1To derive a parameter scaling rule for arbitrary p, we extend the techniques developed in Ref.",
    "[7] for MaxCut on large-girth, regular unweighted graphs to large-girth, regular graphs with i.i.d. edge weights.",
    "Without a subscript, |γ, β⟩ will refer to the p-layer QAOA state for a random weighted instance of MaxCut on a given (D + 1)-regular graph with weights, w, drawn from a distribution w. Note that⟨C(γ, β)⟩ = 1 2 {u,v}∈E w uv (1 -⟨γ, β|z u z v |γ, β⟩).",
    "(51)We start by proving the following result about the above quantity that is valid for any p. E w [⟨C(γ, β)⟩] = N (D + 1)µ 4 - N (D + 1) 4 E w [w⟨γ, β|z L z R |γ, β⟩],(52)for any edge {L, R}.",
    "The locality of the p-layer QAOA combined with the regularity and girth > 2p + 1 assumptions implies that the quantity w LR ⟨γ, β|z L z R |γ, β⟩ can only depend on vertices that lie in a D-ary tree of diameter 2p + 1."
